Part 3: Logical statements
‚Äúif statements‚Äù can be very useful. They work as follows:
if (the logical statement in these parentheses is TRUE) {
  do this} 
else {
  do that
}
Let‚Äôs try it.

## Example 1:
if (2 + 2 == 5) {
  print("Yikes")
} else {
  print("Good job!")
}

[1] "Good job!"



## Example 2:
if (vec1[2] == 2) {
  print("Hello")
}else {
  print("Goodbye")
}

[1] "Hello"

Exercise 4: Logical Statements
Simple if-else: Write an if-else statement that prints ‚ÄúBig‚Äù if the average of numbers is greater than 10, and ‚ÄúSmall‚Äù otherwise.


Sample Solution
# Simple if-else
if (mean(numbers) &gt; 10) {
  print("Big")
} else {
  print("Small")
}


Nested if-else: Modify the above to include a check if the average is exactly 10, printing ‚ÄúExactly 10‚Äù.


Sample Solution
# Nested if-else
if (mean(numbers) == 10) {
  print("Exactly 10")
} else if (mean(numbers) &gt; 10) {
  print("Big")
} else {
  print("Small")
}

